athletes.Biography: Paul Michael Santoro is an professional gamer, commentator, host, emcee, streamer, content creator and public speaker turned Executive, with over 15 years experience in the video game and esports industry. His work in esports has included, being one of the first, multi-genre professional gamers, winning in both Gears of War and Dead or Alive Fighting Game Franchises at the same time. His experience has encompassed competing and commentating in over 100 LANs and productions since 2004.- - His most notable work includes, being featured in Xbox and Playstation magazines as part of the "I'm a Fighter" marketing campaign, and starring in multiple gaming based reality shows like the "Infinite Crisis Experience" produced by Jace Hall and Twin Galaxies. As well as, Hirez Studios "The Caster" and Activision-Blizzards "Friday Night Fights" for Call of Duty. He has also worked with the NBA 2K League as an in-arena emcee and host for Season 2 of their live production.- View more...

athletes.Name: Alison Gibson
athletes.Biography: Sports were always about accomplishing something bigger than myself. Above all else, my dream was to use my success in my sport to impact the next generations of athletes and help prepare them for the turbulent rollercoaster of elite athletics. In college as SAAC president I worked with other athletes to start on organization called DNA designed to raise money that is then invested back into buying supplies and gear for athletes form less fortunate families. The program is still running strong today. I also coach private lessons and whenever I have the change I find ways to invest in your athletes and use my personal successes and failures to inspire them to continue on their pursuits of their dreams. To me, going to the Olympics was more about representing my country or coming home with a metal, it was about being a role model for the young athletes watching. I told myself, no matter what happens, my one goal is to use this experience to impact just one life, and I did that.
